Tunable.description: If checked, any Sim may score, even if their team is not considered active.

TunableVariant.name: ending_condition
TunableVariant.description: The condition under which the game ends.

TunableTuple.name: round_based
TunableTuple.description: A game that ends after a certain number of rounds. The Team with the highest score at that point wins.

Tunable.name: rounds
Tunable.description: Length of game (in rounds).

TunableTuple.name: score_based
TunableTuple.description: A game that ends when one of the teams wins by reaching a certain score first

Tunable.name: winning_score
Tunable.description: Score required to win.

Tunable.name: persist_high_score
Tunable.description: If checked, the high score and the team Sim ids will be saved onto the game component.

Tunable.name: progress_stat
Tunable.description: The statistic that advances the progress state of this game.

Tunable.name: relevant_skill
Tunable.description: The skill relevant to this game. Each Sim's proficiency in this skill will effect the score increase they get.

TunableTuple.name: score_increase
TunableTuple.description: An interval specifying the minimum and maximum score increases possible in one turn. A random value in this interval will be generated each time score loot is given.

Tunable.name: lower_bound
Tunable.description: The lower bound of the interval.

Tunable.name: upper_bound
Tunable.description: The upper bound of the interval.

Tunable.name: skill_level_bonus
Tunable.description:
A bonus number of points based on the Sim's skill level in the relevant_skill tunable that will be added to score_increase.
ex: If this value is 2 and the Sim receiving score has a relevant skill level of 4, they will receive 8 (2 * 4) extra points.

Tunable.name: use_effective_skill_level
Tunable.description: If checked, we will use the effective skill level rather than the actual skill level of the relevant_skill tunable.

TunableVariant.name: team_strategy
TunableVariant.description: Define how Sims are distributed across teams.

TunableTuple.name: auto_balanced
TunableTuple.description: Sims will automatically distribute themselves in teams. The game attempts to keep teams well-balanced.

TunableTuple.name: part_driven
TunableTuple.description: Sims will be part of teams as defined by part adjacency.

Tunable.name: _team_determines_part
Tunable.description: If True, the team a sim is added to determines which parts can be used. If false, the part a team chooses to use determines which team the sim should be on.

TunableVariant.name: part_requirement
TunableVariant.description: Define how part relationships define team structure.

TunableTuple.name: adjacent
TunableTuple.description: Sims using adjacent parts are on the same team. This only supports simple situations where we assume all parts forming a team are adjacent.

TunableTuple.name: teams_per_game
TunableTuple.description:
An interval specifying the number of teams allowed per game.
Joining Sims are put on a new team if the maximum number of teams has not yet been met, otherwise they are put into the team with the fewest number of players.

Tunable.name: lower_bound
Tunable.description: The lower bound of the interval.

Tunable.name: upper_bound
Tunable.description: The upper bound of the interval.
